      "m3:ontologyType": {
        "@id": "m3:Poclet"
      },
      "rdfs:label": "Bipolar Junction Transistor (BJT) - NPN Configuration",
      "rdfs:comment": "BJT as electronic Processor: Input (base current, collector voltage) → Amplification/Switching → Output (collector current). Minimal complete semiconductor processor demonstrating dual modes (linear amplification vs digital switching). Validates Processor GenericConcept with continuous analog inputs/outputs and transformation via charge carrier control.",
      "dcterms:creator": "Echopraxium with the collaboration of Claude AI",
      "dcterms:created": "2026-02-07",
      "owl:versionInfo": "15.2.0",
      "m1:domain": [ "Electronics", "Semiconductor Physics", "Analog Electronics", "Signal Processing", "Circuit Theory" ], 
      "m2:changelog": [
        "2026-02-24: v15.2.0 — Replaced m0:dualModes with comprehensive m0:operatingModes covering BJT (4 modes: Cutoff, Forward Active, Saturation, Reverse Active) and MOSFET NMOS (3 modes: Cutoff, Triode, Saturation). Added namingConventionNote on BJT/MOSFET Saturation inversion. Added comparativeTable (BJT↔MOSFET mode equivalences). Updated m0:simulation for new device-selector tab (BJT/MOSFET) and mode panel. versionInfo 15.1.0 → 15.2.0.",
        "2026-02-24: v15.1.0 — Fixed @context URIs to canonical tscg GitHub raw path. Added m0:simulation property documenting transistor_sim.py (I-V characteristic curves, live operating-point display, ASFID/REVOI panels). Added m0:operatingRegionColors for simulation. versionInfo bumped 15.0.0 → 15.1.0.",
        "2026-02-07: v15.0.0 — Initial creation. BJT as first electronic Processor poclet. Validates Processor ternary hybrid formulas (Territory: Transformation⊗Flow⊗Resource; Map: Transformation⊗Representation⊗Interoperability). 11 GenericConcepts. ASFID=0.85, REVOI=0.86, ΔΘ=0.01."
      ],
      "m0:simulation": {
        "filename": "transistor_sim.py",
        "version": "2.0",
        "description": "Interactive Pygame simulation with device-selector tab (BJT NPN / MOSFET NMOS). Each device shows its full operating mode table with the live mode highlighted, I-V characteristic curves, animated schematic, and ASFID/REVOI panels. Mode colors consistent with m0:operatingModes.",
